Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve, core, and seed @long green pepper{1}, then cut into ½-inch squares. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}(peeled), then cut into ½-inch pieces. Finely chop one tortilla into small pieces. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{1}, then halve; cut one half into wedges.

Place @whole peeled tomatoes{14%oz can} in a #medium bowl{}. Using your hands, crush them into small pieces.

> TIP: If you have a food processor or blender, you can pulse them in there instead.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and @poblano pepper{1}(halved, cored and seeded) and green pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @cumin{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @chili powder{1/2%tsp} into pot. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in tomatoes, @black beans{13.4%oz can} and their liquid, @water{1/4%cup}, and chopped tortilla. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, stack @corn tortillas{5} and cut in half. Turn 90 degrees and cut in half again so that you have 4 stacks of wedge-shaped chips. Set aside. In a #small bowl{}, stir together lime zest, remaining @chili powder{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}, then place tortillas on it in a single layer. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with zest mixture on both sides. Bake in oven until crisp, ~{8-10%minutes}, flipping halfway through. Immediately season with @salt{} once done. Meanwhile, in another small bowl, mix together @sour cream{4%tbsp}, half the @hot sauce{1%tsp}, and juice from lime half. Season with salt and pepper.

Once chili is done, give it a check and add a splash of water if very thick. Divide between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and dollop with crema. Drizzle with remaining hot sauce to taste. Serve with chips and lime wedges on the side.